collections.name: my life and my tree
collections.description:
This work is a visualization of the flow of inner emotions and thoughts through freely flowing curves against the backdrop of the great order of nature. The trees and forest in the background symbolize the chaos and order of nature at the same time, and the inverted image explores the boundaries between reality and unreality, the visible and the hidden. 
The lines that cross it represent unrestrained freedom and the movement of complex emotions. The movement of the lines intentionally does not follow simple rules, reflecting that emotions and thoughts are not fixed but constantly changing. 
This work visually reveals the traces of the inner self within the framework of nature, leaving room for the viewer to discover and interpret their own emotions within these curves.

collections.description:
BORIS WALKS ALONE AGENCY PRESENTS: JAMES BACCHI’S LIMITED-EDITION COLLECTION FOR MODERNISM WEEK

In celebration of the 20th Anniversary of MODERNISM WEEK BORIS WALKS ALONE AGENCY is honored to present a striking new collection of photography by James Bacchi. A resident of Palm Springs, Bacchi is immersed in the very aesthetic that Modernism Week celebrates—surrounded by the timeless architecture, bold design, and storied history that define this iconic destination.

With his signature style of capturing “tension” from the ground up, Bacchi’s black-and-white imagery transforms architectural moments into dramatic, cinematic expressions. His deep connection to Palm Springs is evident in every frame, reflecting the beauty and energy of a city where mid-century modernism thrives.

This exclusive collection features 20 unforgettable photographs, each available in a limited edition of just 25 per image.
